        "description": {
            "value": "<p>Originally developed as a body modification by oreads, <em>fleshgems</em> are crystals that can be implanted in the skin of a creature of any ancestry. While a <em>fleshgem</em> can be applied anywhere on the body for cosmetic purposes, the most common usage among adventurers is to implant them at the base of the fingers, to be used like brass knuckles.</p>\n<p>These pointed crystal shards embedded in your fingers grant you a fist Strike that deals [[/r {1d6}[piercing]]]{1d6 piercing damage}, is in the brawling group, and has the magical and unarmed traits. Combat fleshgems can be enhanced with the effects of <em>handwraps of mighty blows</em>, as normal for an unarmed attack.</p>"
